==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[ab]] "away from" and Greek scopos "a target for shooting at." Term first described by Dr. R. J. Mole in 1953 in the ''British Journal of Radiology'', "Whole body irradiation- radiobiology or medicine?" . Br. J. Radiol., 26: 234-241, 1953.
===Adjective===
'''abscopal'''

# Denoting the effect that irradiation of a tissue has on remote nonirradiated tissue. 
#:''The regression of a liver tumor after irradiation of bone that the tumor metastasized to is an example of the abscopal effect.''